[h3 id=Comments 
	" Comments
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"This map helps you understand the route: 
	[a class=extlink href=http://www.vgmaps.com/Atlas/GB-GBC/index.htm#RolansCurse rel=nofollow 
		"http://www.vgmaps.com/Atlas/GB-GBC/index.htm#RolansCurse
	]a
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"These maps help even more: http://www.gamefaqs.com/portable/gameboy/game/585884.html
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"I get two "armor" item drops from the enemies to boost maximum HP temporarily. "Healing" drops are also manipulated many times. All the item drops are fairly common and easily manipulated, but the health management needs to be planned carefully anyway.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The pick axe (which can be used to destroy certain obstacles) is not a necessary item, but it saves time in the room before the boss.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=BossFight 
	" Boss Fight
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The boss has 255 hit points (RAM address: C23E).
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The player's standard attack power is worth 2 points of damage.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Luckily, there is a power-up just outside the boss room, which increases attack power to 4.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Some time is wasted to save health for the boss room. This allows the player to suicide inside the boss instead of waiting for his fixed movement pattern.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=DeathGlitch 
	" Death Glitch
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The rest of the game is skipped by dying simultaneously with the first boss: The player respawns in the previous room while the boss dies. The level end is then triggered, but due to the focus being in a wrong room, the "final boss is dead" state is summoned instead of the "level 1 boss is dead". I don't know exactly why the game works like that.
	$LF
]p
